{meta: artist Jean Shepard}
{meta: composer Gertrude Cox and Jack Rhodes}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]If you can walk away from me and [F]all my love for [C]you
If you can turn your back upon the [D7]happiness we [G7]knew
[C]I won't even say goodbye I [F]understand we're [C]through
[F]If you can walk [C]away and share your [G7]love with someone [C]new
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
